ocommerce/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"https://wpruby.com/alternatives-woocommerce/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 03 Sep 2017 21:39:16 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"eCommerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://wpruby.com/?p=27198\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:311:\"<p>If you have any reason to move away from the plugin, you might consider the following WooCommerce alternatives.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com/alternatives-woocommerce/\">Alternatives to WooCommerce</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com\">WPRuby</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Waseem\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3291:\"<p>WooCommerce is the most popular eCommerce plugin for WordPress with more than 3 millions active installs and more than 30 millions downloads. WooCommerce has also a very rich extensions collection where you can extend your shop to support more features, or to provide more payment gateways and shipping methods. If you have any reason to move away from the plugin, you might consider the following WooCommerce alternatives.</p>\n<h2><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-e-commerce/\">WP eCommerce</a></h2>\n<p>WP eCommerce is one of the first eCommerce plugins for WordPress. It was created in 2006 and it supports both physical and digital products.</p>\n<p>The plugin support many payment gateways such as Square, Stripe, and Paypal. And many other extensions in order to add additional features in the plugin. Moreover, the plugin has hundreds of <a href=\"https://wpruby.com/wordpress-what-is-the-difference-between-actions-and-filters/\">WordPress hooks</a> that can be used by developers to write their own extensions.</p>\n<h2><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wordpress-ecommerce/\">MarketPress</a></h2>\n<p>MarketPress was created by the popular WordPress plugins provider <a href=\"https://premium.wpmudev.org/\">WPMU DEV</a>, The plugin description says that it&#8217;s the only premium and at the same time completely free.  MarketPress is also supporting selling physical and digital products, and it includes more than 15 payment gateways. One of the selling points of MarketPress is that it&#8217;s compatible with Multisite and BuddyPress, that means you can create multiple stores websites.</p>\n<h2><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/jigoshop-ecommerce/\">Jigoshop</a></h2>\n<p>Jigoshop is a good WooCommerce alternative. It&#8217;s no surprise because WooCommerce started as a fork of JigoShop. The plugin is still in active development and recently it had new owners. The plugin has many extensions and themes, and it can be extended by using <a href=\"https://wpruby.com/wordpress-what-is-the-difference-between-actions-and-filters/\">WordPress hooks</a>.</p>\n<h2><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ithemes-exchange/\">iThemes Exchange</a></h2>\n<p>This plugin is for minimalists, it&#8217;s one of the simplest eCommerce plugins where you can use it to kickstart the selling process as fast as possible without a lot of a hassle in the different eCommerce settings and options. Even though the plugin provides the minimal features, it has many add-ons in order to extend your shop.</p>\n<h2>Other plugins</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ecwid-shopping-cart/\">Ecwid Ecommerce Shopping Cart</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ecommerce-wd/\">eCommerce WD – eCommerce shopping cart plugin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/powr-ecommerce/\">eCommerce by POWr.io</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wpshop/\">WPshop &#8211; eCommerce</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/cart66-cloud/\">Cart66 Cloud :: Ecommerce with security</a></li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"et_bloom_bottom_trigger\"></span><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com/alternatives-woocommerce/\">Alternatives to WooCommerce</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com\">WPRuby</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"https://wpruby.com/alternatives-woocommerce/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"Top Key Performance Indicators for eCommerce Businesses\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://wpruby.com/top-key-performance-indicators-ecommerce-businesses/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"https://wpruby.com/top-key-performance-indicators-ecommerce-businesses/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 27 Aug 2017 22:22:37 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"eCommerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://wpruby.com/?p=27162\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:463:\"<p>When it comes to eCommerce businesses, there are certain key performance indicators that can be beneficial to measure the eCommerce venture health. Here is a list of the top X KPIs for eCommerce businesses.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com/top-key-performance-indicators-ecommerce-businesses/\">Top Key Performance Indicators for eCommerce Businesses</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com\">WPRuby</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Waseem\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8608:\"<p>Key performance indicators (KPIs) are the main metrics to monitor in order to retain your online business success. They can be an early alert if something is going wrong in your business operations. Moreover, they help you to observe your progress towards your sales, revenue and your business goals.</p>\n<p>A performance indicator is a measure that can be quantified or simply a number that represents an aspect of your business data. For instance, if one of your business goals this year is to increase sales by 40%, then you have to look at certain indicator to observe your progress to achieve this goal. In this case, you might need to monitor the monthly total sales as this indicator of the sales at the end of the year.</p>\n<p>Take into consideration that one business goals may need many indicators in order to have an overall overview of the goal performance indication.</p>\n<p>When it comes to eCommerce businesses, there are certain key performance indicators that can be beneficial to measure the eCommerce venture health. Here is a list of the top X KPIs for eCommerce businesses.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Average Acquisition Cost</h2>\n<p>This indicator is used to measure the total cost to acquire a new customer. This metric can be also used to measure the efficiency of your acquisition channels.<br />\nYour aim is to reduce the acquisition cost as much as possible. Thus, you have to regularly check your marketing channels cost and make sure to pay for the channels that actually converts the traffic into paying customers. Paying for marketing channels that do not convert to customers can harm your profit margin.</p>\n<h3>How to calculate Average Acquisition Cost?</h3>\n<p>Primarily, you can calculate the Average Acquisition Cost by dividing the total costs spent on acquiring new customers (marketing expenses) by the number of customers acquired in the period the money was spent. Let&#8217;s say that your business spent $100 on marketing in a month and acquired 20 customers in the same month, then your Average Acquisition Cost is $5.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Average margin</h2>\n<p>After subtracting all of the supplying costs of the product, you end up with your net profit from each product. For this product, this is the margin profit of this product. To maintain a sustainable eCommerce business, you need to keep your average margin higher than the average acquisition cost.</p>\n<p>Some of your products might have a high margin but on the other hand, other products might have low margin. That&#8217;s normal. And that&#8217;s why you need to keep an eye on the average margin of your business.</p>\n<p>Another thing you can do to increase your margin is to negotiate a lower cost of the products with your suppliers. This would help you to earn more by increasing your margin without raising your online shop prices. Thus, eliminating the possibility of customers not buying because of the price sensitivity.</p>\n<p>In general, you should keep checking on your margins routinely in order to attain a healthy profitable business.</p>\n<h3>How to calculate Average margin?</h3>\n<p>The average margin can be easily calculated by subtracting the total revenue of the period (e.g. monthly) from the total expenses cost of the same period then divide the outcome by the total number of products in your shop.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Cart Abandonment Rate</h2>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-27181 size-full\" src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/abandoned-cart.jpg\" alt=\"Cart Abandonment Rate\" width=\"1000\" height=\"585\" srcset=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/abandoned-cart.jpg 1000w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/abandoned-cart-300x176.jpg 300w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/abandoned-cart-768x449.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></p>\n<p>With an average of 68% cart abandonment rate in the eCommerce industry. One must consider reducing this indicator value as much as possible.<br />\nThere are different causes of your customers ending abandoning their carts:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Complicated checkout process such as asking the customer to fill up a lengthy checkout form or requiring her to have a membership on the website in order to complete the checkout.</li>\n<li>Hidden costs that customers find out about in the checkout process such as taxes or high shipping fees.</li>\n<li>Limited payment options. some users may have no access to your store payment gateways, this will be a burden for them to complete the checkout.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>In order to reduce cart abandonment rate, you need to reduce the friction of the checkout process and makes it as smooth as possible by solving all possible causes and even by reaching out to customers directly and ask them for the reason behind the abandonment and trying to solve their concern.</p>\n<h3>How to calculate Cart Abandonment Rate?</h3>\n<p>You can directly calculate it by getting these values (Total Checkout Initiations, Completed Purchases)<br />\nThen we have Not Completed Purchases = Total Checkout Initiations &#8211; Completed Purchases.<br />\nThen you need to divide the Not Completed Purchases by the Total Checkout Initiations.</p>\n<h4>Example:</h4>\n<p>Clothes store have 300 orders this month, and their customers initiated checkout 700 times.<br />\nThen the Not completed Purchases = 700 &#8211; 300 = 400 purchases.<br />\nThen the Cart Abandonment Rate = (400 / 700) * 100 = 57%</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Returns (Refund) Rate</h2>\n<p>Some eCommerce niches have a high return rate such as clothing, it is obvious why, isn&#8217;t it? Even in almost all of other niches, people return the products due to various reasons. A high return rate can be very dangerous to your business, it indicates that there might a problem in the quality of the products, or customers simply are not satisfied with it.</p>\n<p>Collecting a feedback from customers that returned a product is a must. This will help you get an overview of common causes of the returns and take steps further to eliminate them. Also, provide as much as you can of product&#8217;s details on the product page in order to let your customers know what exactly they are purchasing. A good quality product&#8217;s images are very helpful. Furthermore, you need to have a refund policy where users explicitly agree on it during the checkout process.</p>\n<h3>How to calculate Returns Rate?</h3>\n<p>Return Rate is calculated as the percentage of product returns accepted compared to total sales.<br />\nReturn Rate = (Product Returns / Total Sales) * 100</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Conversion Rate</h2>\n<p>Conversion Rate is one of the most important and crucial indicators for any eCommerce business. It&#8217;s the indicator that tells you how many of your traffic that actually becoming paying customers. You can probably get tons of traffic but with not a single sale.<br />\nMany reasons can be the reason of a low conversion rate, such as a bad website design, non-quality leads, no secure connection (SSL certificate), not enough details in the products pages, or bad quality products images.</p>\n<p>For a better conversion rate measurement, it&#8217;s recommended to segment the traffic into sales funnels in order to calculate each marketing channel or traffic source own conversion rate. This will simplify the Rate Conversion optimization process for you.</p>\n<h3>How to calculate Conversion Rate?</h3>\n<p>The Conversion Rate can be easily calculated by dividing the number of paying customers by the total traffic. And you can measure conversion rate for each marketing channel by replacing the numbers that are coming from that channel.<br />\nConversion Rate = (Total number of paying customers / Total Traffic)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Other important indicators</h2>\n<h3>Customer Lifetime Value</h3>\n<p>Customer Lifetime Value indicates how much individual customers spent on your eCommerce website. It’s calculated by subtracting the acquisition cost from the revenue earned from each customer.</p>\n<h3>Support Rate</h3>\n<p>Support Rate stress how many visitors or potential customers require customer support before they purchase a product. If this metric is high you should think about adding more information to the website in order to reduce the rate of support tickets opening.</p>\n<span class=\"et_bloom_bottom_trigger\"></span><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com/top-key-performance-indicators-ecommerce-businesses/\">Top Key Performance Indicators for eCommerce Businesses</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com\">WPRuby</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://wpruby.com/top-key-performance-indicators-ecommerce-businesses/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"6 Economical Digital Marketing Advice for an Ecommerce Business\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://wpruby.com/6-economical-digital-marketing-advice-for-an-ecommerce-business/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"https://wpruby.com/6-economical-digital-marketing-advice-for-an-ecommerce-business/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 26 Aug 2017 14:48:52 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"eCommerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://wpruby.com/?p=27005\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:503:\"<p>Do you just start selling products online and your business does not have a big number budget for digital marketing? Well, we present to you some digital marketing tips that you can afford when you start your ecommerce business.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com/6-economical-digital-marketing-advice-for-an-ecommerce-business/\">6 Economical Digital Marketing Advice for an Ecommerce Business</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com\">WPRuby</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Waseem\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3967:\"<p>Do you just start selling products online and your business does not have a big number budget for digital marketing? Well, we present to you some digital marketing tips that you can afford when you start your ecommerce business.</p>\n<h2>1. Do not fall for the Boost Your Post button on Facebook</h2>\n<p>It&#8217;s tempting to click on the boost button. But it&#8217;s not the best way to spend your money on Facebook ads. This method will help you reach a general audience group. But as you are selling specific products you need to skip this Boost button. And instead, use the Facebook Ad Manager to use it for targeting a specific niche of users that would be interested in your product/s.</p>\n<h2>2. Don&#8217;t use Twitter Ads, but use Twitter as platform to seek customers</h2>\n<p>Simply, use the Advanced Search Twitter tool to find customers on Twitter, use it to find people who are asking questions about things you sell and answer them from your business Twitter account. Check out this comprehensive guide from Buffer on <a href=\"https://blog.bufferapp.com/twitter-advanced-search\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">how to use Twitter Advanced Search</a>.</p>\n<h2>3. Use Instagram extensively</h2>\n<p>Upload your product images regularly. Better than that, upload your product&#8217;s pictures while they are in use. Use as many as related hashtags to each product. Add your store URL in the Instagram profile. Upload pictures frequently and eventually you would get leads from Instagram.<br />\nRecommended Read: <a href=\"https://www.hubspot.com/instagram-marketing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Instagram Marketing: The Ultimate Guide &#8211; HubSpot</a></p>\n<h2>4. Write about your business, share your journey</h2>\n<p>Leverage online platforms to share your business journey. Write about the challenges you encountered, how did you tackle them. Platforms such as LinkedIn, Medium and Quora can be valuable to attract potential customers or even future partners.</p>\n<h2>5. Email Marketing</h2>\n<p>Do not buy random mail lists from the internet and start sending mass emails to them. This is the worst thing you can do to your business. Take the time and effort to collect users emails by using Landing Pages, ask customers to subscribe to your email list to the checkout page. Include a subscription form on your website pages. If you do this, you&#8217;ll get a list of interested people in your business who are going to come back to your website and moreover they will recommend your business to their social circles.</p>\n<h2>6. Take advantage of attending events</h2>\n<p>Look for events that are related to your domain. There you can find relevant people to connect with them. You might find persons whom you can learn from their success stories, learn new methods to grow your business. Additionally, Keeping yourself updated on the latest progress of your niche is important to your business. You can find events by using platforms such as <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/\">Eventbrite</a> and <a href=\"https://www.meetup.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Meetup</a>.</p>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>Be aware that success needs time, and if you focus on becoming more engaging with your business. Then over time, you&#8217;ll find yourself spending less time on marketing in order to keep sales going.Moreover, do not rush over here and there to spend your money on Ads platforms without carefully planning the return of these paid ads. Spending money on these platforms without planning the result before hands is a disaster for any business. Knowing exactly why are you paying for ads is what makes ads platforms beneficial.</p>\n<span class=\"et_bloom_bottom_trigger\"></span><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com/6-economical-digital-marketing-advice-for-an-ecommerce-business/\">6 Economical Digital Marketing Advice for an Ecommerce Business</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com\">WPRuby</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"https://wpruby.com/6-economical-digital-marketing-advice-for-an-ecommerce-business/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:44:\"Ruby Help Desk is available on WordPress.org\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"https://wpruby.com/help-desk-wordpress-plugin/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://wpruby.com/help-desk-wordpress-plugin/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 18 Aug 2017 18:45:40 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://wpruby.com/?p=25611\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:427:\"<p>A lot of effort is put into gaining clients and capturing market share. Companies spend millions of dollars on advertising to gain clients; once those clients come through the door, no one wants to lose them.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com/help-desk-wordpress-plugin/\">Ruby Help Desk is available on WordPress.org</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com\">WPRuby</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Waseem\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7976:\"<p>A lot of effort is put into gaining clients and capturing market share. Companies spend millions of dollars on advertising to gain clients; once those clients come through the door, no one wants to lose them. Focusing on customer satisfaction is critical because happy clients become repeat clients. Maintaining clients is even more important for small businesses. To offer a small help for online businesses that are based on WordPress, we recently released a Ruby Help Desk which is Help desk WordPress plugin available for free on WordPress.org plugins repository. We assured to make the plugin as simple as possible in order to be</p>\n<h2>Customers Interface</h2>\n<div class=\"su-custom-gallery su-custom-gallery-title-never su-lightbox-gallery\"><div class=\"su-custom-gallery-slide\"><a href=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-1.png\" title=\"screenshot-1\"><img src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-1-230x150.png\" alt=\"screenshot-1\" width=\"230\" height=\"150\" /><span class=\"su-custom-gallery-title\">screenshot-1</span></a></div><div class=\"su-custom-gallery-slide\"><a href=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-2.png\" title=\"screenshot-2\"><img src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-2-230x150.png\" alt=\"screenshot-2\" width=\"230\" height=\"150\" /><span class=\"su-custom-gallery-title\">screenshot-2</span></a></div><div class=\"su-custom-gallery-slide\"><a href=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-3.png\" title=\"screenshot-3\"><img src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-3-230x150.png\" alt=\"screenshot-3\" width=\"230\" height=\"150\" /><span class=\"su-custom-gallery-title\">screenshot-3</span></a></div><div class=\"su-clear\"></div></div>\n<p>We created the ticket page as simple as we could in order to work seamlessly on any WordPress theme. WordPress coding standards have been taken into considerations.Your customers won&#8217;t find any</p>\n<p>Your customers won&#8217;t find any difficulties to use the helpdesk efficiently. A straightforward UI which makes your customers. The submit ticket page is fully customizable to suit your business nature needs.</p>\n<h2>Dashboard Widget</h2>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-25624\" src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"374\" srcset=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-4.png 855w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-4-300x187.png 300w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-4-768x479.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<p>The dashboard widget is where administrators have a quick access to the latest submitted tickets and an extra stats about the helpdesk&#8217;s tickets. It shows the number of tickets that are waiting for a response, the tickets in progress, the closed tickets, and the total number of tickets. Moreover, it shows the latest 5 tickets with their statuses.</p>\n<h2>Custom Fields</h2>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-25627\" src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-7.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-7.png 1281w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-7-300x129.png 300w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-7-768x331.png 768w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/screenshot-7-1024x441.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /><br />\nYou can use our form builder to fully customize your Submit Ticket page to suit your business needs. You can add an unlimited number of text, lists, checkboxes, radio buttons, text boxes, date fields. Moreover, you can sort and order the fields as you wish. More form fields types are coming in the next releases of the plugin.</p>\n<h2>Knowledgebase</h2>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-25637\" src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-29-at-02.03.29.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"754\" height=\"575\" srcset=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-29-at-02.03.29.png 754w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-29-at-02.03.29-300x229.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 754px) 100vw, 754px\" /></p>\n<p>There a knowledge base system included in the helpdesk plugin, where you can write guides, docs, and tutorials for each one of your products in order to minimize the number of opened tickets.</p>\n<h2>Import WooCommerce and Easy Digital Downloads products</h2>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-25636\" src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-29-at-01.55.35.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1115\" height=\"416\" srcset=\"https://wpruby.com