purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Waseem\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3738:\"<p>2.0 is the third major release of Australia Post WooCommerce Extension Pro plugin. We added two new features and fixed many bugs.</p>\n<h2>Custom Boxes</h2>\n<p>As of the most requested feature, we added the ability to add your own custom boxes information. And the plugin will utilize the shipping calculations based on your own boxes in order to achieve the most accurate price.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-25471\" src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-23-at-11.47.12.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1962\" height=\"714\" srcset=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-23-at-11.47.12.png 1962w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-23-at-11.47.12-300x109.png 300w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-23-at-11.47.12-768x279.png 768w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-23-at-11.47.12-1024x373.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1962px) 100vw, 1962px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Australia Post Tracking</h2>\n<p>Now, you can provide your customers with an easy way to track their shipments. After adding details to an order, the tracking information will appear on the order tracking page and the order view page in their account section.</p>\n<div class=\"su-custom-gallery su-custom-gallery-title-never su-lightbox-gallery\"><div class=\"su-custom-gallery-slide\"><a href=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-23-at-13.47.42-1.png\" title=\"Order page\"><img src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-23-at-13.47.42-1-170x110.png\" alt=\"Order page\" width=\"170\" height=\"110\" /><span class=\"su-custom-gallery-title\">Order page</span></a></div><div class=\"su-custom-gallery-slide\"><a href=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Screen-Shot-2017-06-22-at-22.43.36.png\" title=\"Australia Post Tracking\"><img src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Screen-Shot-2017-06-22-at-22.43.36-170x110.png\" alt=\"Australia Post Tracking\" width=\"170\" height=\"110\" /><span class=\"su-custom-gallery-title\">Australia Post Tracking</span></a></div><div class=\"su-custom-gallery-slide\"><a href=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-23-at-13.47.29.png\" title=\"My Account Page\"><img src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2017-06-23-at-13.47.29-170x110.png\" alt=\"My Account Page\" width=\"170\" height=\"110\" /><span class=\"su-custom-gallery-title\">My Account Page</span></a></div><div class=\"su-clear\"></div></div>\n<p><strong>Some other improvements and bug fixes</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>ADDED</strong>: Compatibility with WC 3.0.</li>\n<li><strong>FIXED</strong>: Satchels box packing.</li>\n<li><strong>FIXED</strong>: Show express services letters only when express is selected.</li>\n<li><strong>FIXED</strong>: Custom titles when satchels are enabled.</li>\n<li><strong>REMOVED</strong>: Legacy settings page, Please use shipping zones with WC 2.6+</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"su-note\" style=\"border-color:#ddda82;border-radius:3px;-moz-border-radius:3px;-webkit-border-radius:3px;\"><div class=\"su-note-inner su-clearfix\" style=\"background-color:#f6f290;border-color:#fdfce9;color:#453d3d;border-radius:3px;-moz-border-radius:3px;-webkit-border-radius:3px;\">We strongly advise to use the built-in WooCommerce shipping zones. As the Legacy settings page of Australia Post is now removed.</div></div>\n<span class=\"et_bloom_bottom_trigger\"></span><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com/australia-post-woocommerce-extension-pro-2-0/\">What&#8217;s new in Australia Post WooCommerce Extension Pro 2.0</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com\">WPRuby</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://wpruby.com/australia-post-woocommerce-extension-pro-2-0/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"WooCommerce: How to set free shipping for certain products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://wpruby.com/woocommerce-set-free-shipping-certain-products/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://wpruby.com/woocommerce-set-free-shipping-certain-products/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 06 Mar 2017 13:03:05 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"How to\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://wpruby.com/?p=22234\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:560:\"<p>Using the free shipping method will not allow you to specify certain products since it does not have the options to accomplish that such as shipping classes. Instead, we are going to use the Flat Rate shipping method. Go to the shipping zone, and add the Flat Rate shipping zone to it. Then, go to [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com/woocommerce-set-free-shipping-certain-products/\">WooCommerce: How to set free shipping for certain products</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com\">WPRuby</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Waseem\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2174:\"<div class=\"su-note\" style=\"border-color:#d6d169;\"><div class=\"su-note-inner su-clearfix\" style=\"background-color:#eee875;border-color:#fcfae3;color:#666967;\">UPDATE: The solution listed in this post is not optimal. Please, take a look and try the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/woo-free-shipping-per-product/\">Free Shipping Per Product For WooCommerce</a> plugin.</div></div>\n<p>Using the free shipping method will not allow you to specify certain products since it does not have the options to accomplish that such as shipping classes. Instead, we are going to use the Flat Rate shipping method.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to the shipping zone, and add the Flat Rate shipping zone to it.</li>\n<li>Then, go to <em>WooCommerce</em> ⇒ <em>Settings</em> ⇒ <em>Shipping</em> ⇒ <em>Shipping Classes</em>, and create a new class and name it &#8216;<em>Free Shipping</em>&#8216;.</li>\n<li>After that, go to the <em>Products</em> page, and select from the table the products you want to set them as free shipping, select the checkboxes, then at the top of the table select Edit from the Bulk Actions, then click apply.</li>\n<li>Set the shipping class of the products to &#8216;Free Shipping&#8217;.</li>\n<li>Now, go to Shipping Zones and click on the &#8216;Flat Rate&#8217; method. You&#8217;ll be redirected to the method&#8217;s settings page.</li>\n<li>Change the name of the method to &#8216;Free Shipping&#8217;.</li>\n<li>Finally, set the &#8220;Free Shipping&#8221; Shipping Class Cost option to <em>0</em>.</li>\n<li>Save the changes and now only the products that have the &#8216;<em>Free Shipping</em>&#8216; class will have a free shipping.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>There are other methods such as using Table Rate Shipping plugins to create conditions. But this method does not require any plugins since it uses the Flat Rate method which comes bundled with WooCommerce.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<span class=\"et_bloom_bottom_trigger\"></span><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com/woocommerce-set-free-shipping-certain-products/\">WooCommerce: How to set free shipping for certain products</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com\">WPRuby</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://wpruby.com/woocommerce-set-free-shipping-certain-products/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"What’s new in WooCommerce Australia Post 1.9\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"https://wpruby.com/whats-new-woocommerce-australia-post-1-9/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"https://wpruby.com/whats-new-woocommerce-australia-post-1-9/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 19 Feb 2017 19:44:02 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"eCommerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://wpruby.com/?p=21420\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:370:\"<p>1.9 is the third major release of WooCommerce Australia Post Shipping Method plugin. We added two new features and fixed many bugs.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com/whats-new-woocommerce-australia-post-1-9/\">What&#8217;s new in WooCommerce Australia Post 1.9</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com\">WPRuby</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Waseem\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2668:\"<p>1.9 is the third major release of WooCommerce Australia Post Shipping Method plugin. We added two new features and fixed many bugs.</p>\n<h3>Now, you can rename the shipping services</h3>\n<p>This was the most requested feature in the last two months. So we decided to include it in this release. With 1.9, you can rename the shipping services of Australia Post. This includes domestic, international and letters options. Keep in mind renaming a shipping option will rename only the service name in the cart and checkout pages but not the delivery time text. We have no control over the delivery time text.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-21421\" src=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-19-at-20.28.54-1024x811.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2017-02-19 at 20.28.54\" width=\"960\" height=\"760\" srcset=\"https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-19-at-20.28.54-1024x811.png 1024w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-19-at-20.28.54-300x238.png 300w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-19-at-20.28.54-768x608.png 768w, https://wpruby.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Screen-Shot-2017-02-19-at-20.28.54.png 1073w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></p>\n<h3>A new option to set a falling price</h3>\n<p>The plugin will display this price in case Australia Post service doesn&#8217;t return any prices or any other reason. Leave it blank to disable the fallback price functionality.</p>\n<p><strong>Some other improvements and bug fixes</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fixed</strong>: Calculating handling fees.</li>\n<li><strong>Fixed</strong>: Letters calculations.</li>\n<li><strong>Fixed</strong>: WC() fatal error.</li>\n<li><strong>Fixed</strong>: Max weight for satchels.</li>\n<li><strong>Fixed</strong>: Signature on Delivery and Extra Cover fees showing when free shipping selected.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"su-note\" style=\"border-color:#ddda82;border-radius:3px;-moz-border-radius:3px;-webkit-border-radius:3px;\"><div class=\"su-note-inner su-clearfix\" style=\"background-color:#f6f290;border-color:#fdfce9;color:#453d3d;border-radius:3px;-moz-border-radius:3px;-webkit-border-radius:3px;\">We strongly advise to use the built-in WooCommerce shipping zones. As the Legacy settings page of Australia Post will be removed in the future releases.</div></div>\n<span class=\"et_bloom_bottom_trigger\"></span><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com/whats-new-woocommerce-australia-post-1-9/\">What&#8217;s new in WooCommerce Australia Post 1.9</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpruby.com\">WPRuby</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://wpruby.com/whats-new-woocommerce-australia-post-1-9/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n	